- Generated ICMP Echo Request and Echo Reply packets
- Observed real-time connectivity between host and external server

---

### 2. DNS Traffic Analysis
- Applied Wireshark filter:

- Observed domain name resolution requests (e.g., google.com, example.com)
- Understood how domain names are translated into IP addresses

---

### 3. HTTP Traffic Analysis
- Generated HTTP traffic using:

- Observed GET requests and server responses

---

## 🔍 Key Observations
- ICMP is used for network reachability testing
- DNS resolves human-readable domains into IP addresses
- HTTP is used for retrieving web content from servers
- Network traffic can be filtered and analyzed in real time using Wireshark

